08/08/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Seven people were killed by extensive flooding in several Bulgarian towns on Tuesday (August 7th). 
Six elderly people died in the northeastern town of Tsar Kaloyan when flash floods hit the area. 
Rescue workers are trying to locate three people, including a child, who were reported missing after the first wave hit the lower section of the small town. 
The army has been called in to bring water and help in the cleanup effort. 
A state of emergency also has been declared in the southern city of Pazardzhik, where public buildings have flooded. 
An elderly man drowned in a village near the northern Danube port of Ruse. 
The ski resort of Bansko also reported flood damage. 
(DPA, Reuters, BBC - 07/08/07)
